column5: Hi all,  managed to get down to Eagle lake again, seems the walleye have started to show more consistently ( ok Benbeattie....some of us dont have the magic touch  ), hoping they come to my bay for spring as they did 2 years ago....anyway........went with my buddy Matt......     PICKED MATT UP ABOUT 4pm         WE DRILLED A LOT OF HOLES FROM 28' to 12', I GOT THE FIRST RESPECTABLE FISH            AFTER NOT MUCH LUCK FOR 3 HOURS MATT GOT A NICE 19", BUT IN THE SLOT SO BACK IT WENT....YOUR CHICKENS COULD BE IN TROUBLE MATT!        MATT GOT ANOTHER SMALLISH KEEPER AND I ADDED THIS TO OUR FEED.        BEST PICTURE OF THE DAY GOES TO BABY LIMEY THOUGH

Niiiiice Simon.  You're holding your own down there.  Some real nice walleye.  Cute pic there too, Dad.  Today we're taking probably our last crack at the first spot we went to with you.  We'll see how it goes.
Great report, pics and video Simon  OK... in the video department.... that was somewhat better    J/K LOL Nice eyes and great job you guys  Loved the last pic!! Awesome!! Thanks for sharing Jacques

You're already out there slaying 'em as i reply....but good luck all the same.     LOLOL Jacques....i actually did the video with you in mind as you have rightly pointed out i'''ve been slack in the video department recently....all the chickens are still alive....for now....hehe.
Your too kind Simon   :lol: Are you sure you didn't have a chicken salad sandwich with them eyes
